It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. This is the last room in the house that has only been simply decorated.
Take down the ugly electric fireplace and the bed. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Custom-order a wardrobe.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
A few dead birds were found behind the chimney, their bodies completely dried up :(
Prepare for the plasterers next week
Happy with the small niche next to it
Put the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet 😅)
Ha ha, look what we found behind the radiator!
Remember the cute little vent we added to prevent the chimney from getting damp
Sweep has installed the chimney cover and chimney cap. The white robins that like to nest in the chimney should now be safer. 🪺
The plasterers have finished their work. We will lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork padding has been laid down, and a roll of toilet paper was used to make a attachment for the vacuum cleaner to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared and is ready to start laying. Let's have a cup of tea and take a break.
Well, today's progress was a bit slow, because in order to seamlessly connect with the corridor (which is also being laid with floor), cutting around the door frame was needed, which was quite tedious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me
Finally finished, but it's all mess! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed are terrible. Finally, I can sleep well tonight!
There's still the corridor floor and baseboard left. The decorator comes a month later, so we can only make do now, with just bare drywall in the room.
Last night did a simple DIY, using a dovetail saw and chisel to cut part of the door frame bottom, so the floor can perfectly fit underneath.
The softwood underlayment in the corridor is also laid.
Yesterday we also laid the floor in the corridor! Today morning I got up at 5 a.m. to go to Heathrow Airport to pick up the first package, then had a nap, and now finally can start installing the baseboard in the corridor. Wait until the glue dries before filling the gaps.
